   "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
   "body" : "The existing block generation rpcs for regtest, `generatetoaddress` and `generatetodescriptor`, mine everything in the mempool within consensus limits. This makes it difficult to test a system for several situations where a different set of transactions are mined. For example:\r\n- Testing the common situation where a transaction is replaced in the mempool but the previously replaced transaction is mined.\r\n- Testing for a double-spent transaction where a transaction that conflicts with the mempool is mined.\r\n- Testing for non-standard transactions that are mined.\r\n\r\nThis PR introduces a new rpc, `generatecustomblock`, that takes an array of either raw transactions or txids and mines only those and the coinbase. Any txids must be in the mempool, but the raw txs can be anything conforming to consensus rules. The coinbase can be specified as either an address or descriptor.\r\n\r\nThere is some relevant conversation [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/15873#issuecomment-485993758). ",
